<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id83b39b6c-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s116"><num value="116">§ 116.</num><heading> Technical data</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this subtitle, the term “technical data”—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id83b39b6d-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s116/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> means recorded information (regardless of the form or method of the recording) of a scientific or technical nature (including computer software documentation) relating to supplies procured by an agency; but</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id83b39b6e-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s116/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> does not include computer software or financial, administrative, cost or pricing, or management data or other information incidental to contract administration.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id83b39b6f-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/350/s3">Pub. L. 111–350, § 3</ref>, <date date="2011-01-04">Jan. 4, 2011</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3681">124 Stat. 3681</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
